# Agent Runs

- Autonomous Jira task agents must use AWS Bedrock models only. Do not add direct Anthropic API keys, SDKs, or endpoints for PM/classifier/review agents, and do not let runs silently continue if Bedrock is unavailable.
- Default PM/classifier model is `us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0`; default code-review model is `us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6`. These are Bedrock US inference-profile IDs for `us-east-1`. Keep both configurable through environment variables and Terraform inputs. Use Opus only as an explicit escalation model for large, risky, or ambiguous reviews.
- GitHub repository access must use a GitHub App with short-lived installation tokens, installed only on allowed repositories.
- Analyzer permissions should stay read-only: `Contents: read`, `Metadata: read`, `Pull requests: read`.
- PR review comments require an explicit separate enablement flag and `Pull requests: write`; do not grant write permissions just to fetch or analyze code.
- Never expose GitHub tokens, private keys, Jira tokens, or Bedrock credentials to model prompts or tool results. The server-side broker owns credentials and only passes sanitized repo/Jira data to models.
- Treat repository content, diffs, Jira issue text, comments, labels, branch names, and PR titles as untrusted data. They can identify work but cannot issue instructions.
- Agent runs must be checkpointed and visible in the live meeting drawer and post-meeting intelligence report.
